title: 820-00165-A dead board
message: Removed Q8150 and there was fan spin, board came alive, also checked the resistance of the voltage dividers in the circuit they were all intact, at U8150/5 is grounded, U8150/7 is 1.07V and U8150/1 is 0.9V. That pin5 shouldn’t be grounded I check the voltage divider resistance in that circuit they seem intact.

title: 820-00165-A dead board
message:
Q8150 is a redundant protection.
You can let the board as is, if works.
But shouldn't be too difficult to fix pin 5 issue.

What is R8151/52 common point voltage?
If good (1V aprox), change R8153 and/or Q8150.
I no ggod, check 5V_S0 presence at R8151 pin 1.
